rd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 590<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 10:01:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1420.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   heh</span><hr size=1> How am I a hypocrite?  Please do enlighten me.  Do you know the definition of the word? To put it plainly, it means that I&quot;m a hypocrite if -I- use market channel in an ooc fashion, while telling you that it's wrong.  Yet, I always use it in character... so please, do tell me, where am I a hypocrite.<br>
<br>
And if someone wants to ask an entirely ooc question that's related to gameplay, it's simple enough.<br>
<br>
a) create an ooc channel and use it. Yeah yeah nobody uses it, so it's not really feasible. But that's what YOU really want.<br>
<br>
so another more reasonable solution<br>
<br>
b) &quot;ooc: How do I adjust the light settings on my monitor?&quot;<br>
and then the folks that know the answer can /tell the person.<br>
<br>
As to GM events.... what's that got to do with market? Why should folks care about it that are there to buy and sell?  Most Gm events are set up to only involve a limited amount of folks, if suddenly it's announced in market by some overzealous individual, then it defeats the event's purpose.. that of challenging individuals currently present in the zone.  IF a GM wants more participation, they have something called a global announcement channel. I'm sure you've seen it, that bright yellow color going &quot;Arena event in 30 minutes in Lake Rathe... folks of level 30-60 welcome&quot;<br>
<br>
As to shouting cross zone.. that was changed a while back, all shouts go across the zone now.<br>
<br>
As to you telling me that I should leave the market channel if I dont like it... well you are losing yourself a potential buyer for one.  Another, you are actually saying &quot;go away, roleplayers suck&quot; .. well not quite, but close enough.   There should never be a reason for any roleplayer on this server to feel like they dont belong.  There are plenty of other servers to go to for non-roleplayers, where ooc is common.  There is no place for a roleplayer to retreat to from here. Market channel is 100% a roleplayer's domain, just like bazaar, or *gasp* Greater Faydark... <br>
<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://www.sa.il24.net/~saran/kyrial/kyrialsig.jpg">
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthevolcanogod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 10:52:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1420.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: heh</span><hr size=1> A hypocrite is by simple definition someone who doesn't practice what they preach. If you advocate immersing yourself in RP 100% and yet subject yourself by choice to an inherently non-RP arena then you are, by your free actions, a hypocrite.<br>
<br>
Counterpoints:<br>
There is already an OOC channel called 'market'. It is used by players OOC to sell and also for general chat which is legitimized by the silent assent of the masses using the channel (100 players isn't exactly a mass but it's what we got). Despite what the channel name is, it isn't used purely for /auc anymore. The fact is that most people congregate there because it is one of the only active OOC channels regularly used on the server and there is a need for an OOC channel. While idle chatter isn't encouraged, it isn't really discouraged either except by a vocal minority who happen to base many of their arguments on a RP basis which IMHO doesn't apply to an inherently non-RP channel.<br>
<br>
Cross zone shouting in this case means across 2 or more zones. I play a lot in FM and most of the time, I am the only one there. It wouldn't be feasible for me to wander zone-to-zone shouting for help, especially if (if we are still following my example) I am nearly blind because of my graphics problem (this is just an example of an OOC use which is necessary - there are many others).<br>
<br>
I am not saying RP sucks in any way, shape or form. I am and have always advocated a distinction between RP and non-RP. I recognize the value of each, I feel they should be kept seperate and distinct and I feel that there are places and times where each should or shouldn't be used. You can't avoid the facts that market was created to be and still is an OOC arena. I still haven't heard a RP justification for its existence which is necessary if you are going to argue this point. RP should be based on the world of Everquest, and in this world, there is no GOOD way to explain Market, so that by definition negates its validity as an RP arena.<br>
I don't want to make RPers unwelcome, but on the other side I don't feel RPers comming into a non-RP forum and flaming people for being OOC is right. That's like joining a running club and announcing at your weekly meeting &quot;Running sucks, I don't do it and neither should you and if you do I will yell at you. We should all rollerblade instead and since *I* am a member of this club, we should do what *I* want because otherwise you are excluding me and making *me* feel uncomfortable.&quot; Yea, but you are still a member of a *running* club.<br>
<br>
You must be able to separate RP from non-RP and accept the use of both. If you get completely immersed in RP you can get in trouble like those people down it the steam tunnels under Princeton or whatever college during the 70's.<br>
Vulrath<br>
