<br>
But as soon as a person logs into the game, and become their character, everything should be treated as roleplay by default... EVERYTHING.  (Unless indicated ooc'ly.)<br>
<br>
The market channel is by NO means a non-RP arena, except by folks like you.  It's called &quot;market&quot; for crying out loud... not even the standard &quot;auction&quot; it is called on most servers.  Market implies trading and selling, and that's quite feasibly done in character.  As to the fact that it's global and that such things dont exist on the world of Earth... well I roleplay these types of differences as simply being part of Norrath. My character doesn't view getting a tell from someone 10 zones away as strange.. my character doesn't view the fact that we got &quot;zone&quot; in the first place as strange... my character doesn't see global channels as strange... they just ARE.   The rules are different for Norrath than they are for Earth. As such, no, the market channel is not inherently out of character.  Please, do post everywhere for folks to use the ooc channel for the chatter.. the folks that truly are there just listening to buy/sell wont move.. but if you want to help some youngsters, by all means, use it.  It does exist, it's just not as popular.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the way my character views the market channel is different from the way that you (the player) sees it. As such, I'm not a hypocrite. But maybe you are... since you consider a channel named &quot;market&quot; an out of character domain. I'm sure the market channel was created by roleplayers to buy and sell.... and you are simply one of the ones ursurping it from what it's suposed to be. Quite frankly, the fact that you think you are justified in calling it &quot;ooc&quot; is ridiculous to me... if it were ooc, it's be called THAT!<br>
<br>
I also stated, use of the market channel in an ooc fashion is fine. But it should be considered a priviledge, not a right, to speak ooc'ly... aka preface with &quot;ooc:&quot;  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You must be able to separate RP from non-RP and accept the use of both. If you get completely immersed in RP you can get in trouble like those people<br>
                            down it the steam tunnels under Princeton or whatever college during the 70's.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am having a rational, reasonable discussion, a discussion as the player, not as the character. My character would never speak to you about these things. I make a distinction between what my character says, and what I do.. I'm not her, by any means. I wash regularly, unlike her, and my own archery skill sucks.  However... you apparently simply play yourself and not your character. Roleplay is pretending that you are your character. Sometimes your character can be very similar to you, sometimes very different. Heck, Shintou isn't a murdering callous dark elf in real life.. <br>
<br>
The world of Norrath is a fantasy world. It exists so we can pretend the outside world doesn't exist, if only for a little while.  I dont endorse crawling in tunnels late a night in the real world, trust me. Or anything foolish otherwise.  Those players would've gotten into trouble with one thing or another, no real reason to blame roleplaying per se. That's like that dad that neglected his son because his Norrath raids were more important. It's not the fault of Everquest, it's the fault of the player if they cannot distinguish reality from a game.<br>
<br>
As a game, I reserve the right to roleplay and immerse myself entirely. That includes the market channel.  It would not include a channel that's named &quot;ooc&quot;.<br>
<br>
*wonders why nobody else is responding to this*  How do others feel?<br>
<br>
