<br>
Whether we agree on the use of market or not, we both agree on the principle of &quot;respect others and the way they play&quot; (within PnP and the EULA of course), which others did not follow (and I am not naming a specific event because it is irrelevent here).<br>
<br>
As to why and when the channel was created, I cannot say since I wasn't on this server at the time. But I can tell you how it is used now and only very few people attempt to RP over it. Whether it's right or wrong, people use the channel as both /auc and /ooc now despite the name. If you spend time on the channel you already know this. It is beyond the scope of these message boards to explain the sociological issues as to why this all happened, but I can tell you this: I am annoyed when the market channel is cruising along, everyone there seems to be content with the discussions taking place and someone decides to join and police the way everyone is using the channel.<br>
<br>
Go back to my running club analogy and think about how you would feel if you were a member of that group who enjoyed running. Why do you think we were all mostly pissed at Nexen? It wasn't so much the SH exploits it was the attitude and lack of respect for the way others play the game.<br>
